Context:
The School of Dental Health at George Brown College is located at the Waterfront Campus and is known for its diversity and graduates who are in high demand. Students learn from industry qualified faculty using the latest technology in the field at the WAVE Dental Clinics, which includes 24 enclosed dental suites, 75 dental chairs, and additional chairs with x-ray facilities. The clinical space is dedicated to the School of Dental Health and covers nearly 40,000 square feet.

Interested individuals can pre-register for dental services by completing an online registration form or calling 416-415-4547. For a full list of fees and services, they can download the WAVE brochure. The mandate of the WAVE Clinics is to support specific course outcomes and student learning experiences, and clients are accepted on a case by case basis.

George Brown College offers a free Entry Advising service to help match skills, background, and career goals with program options. Information sessions are available for interested individuals to learn more about the programs, have questions answered by faculty and staff, and tour classrooms, labs, and facilities. The contact information for the college is 416-415-2000 (TTY: 1-875-515-5559) and ask.george@georgebrown.ca.

The information contained in the website is subject to change without notice, and it should not be viewed as a representation, offer, or warranty. The college has an acknowledgment of land and offers various ways to stay updated, including signing up for news and events.
